            "weighting": "<dd>14%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 3/08/2026 - 26/10/2026</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L01",
            "mode": "Written",
            "category": "Reflection",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>Starting from week 2, students will complete a weekly lecture reflection on the lecture for that week.</p>\n<p>Reflective practice is also an important part of psychology in research and in clinical work that relies on the ability to examine your own thinking honestly. Reflections are one way we can think about how our own experiences and biases help to shape how we interpret and respond to our external environment. </p>\n<p>Reflections are meant to be personal and we are interested in your own thoughts, ideas, and experiences. Using AI is not advised, but if you use AI, you must reference which tool you used and how you used it – e.g., to check the structure or grammar.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Submit via blackboard.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You cannot defer or apply for an extension for this assessment.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>No late submissions</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You cannot defer or apply for an extension for this assessment.</p>"
        },
